==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lorette
<hw>Lo`rette"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<def>In France, a name for a woman who is supported by her lovers, and
devotes herself to idleness, show, and pleasure; -- so called from the
church of Notre Dame de <etsep>Lorette</etsep>, in Paris, near which
many of them resided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lorettine</ent>⟦br⟧
